<br>
Space creates community, be it a gay community or a roleplaying community (see where I'm going with this?).  It also provides a safe haven from an otherwise hostile environment.  Granted, no community can be completely insular, but it's good to have a safe space to retreat to.<br>
<br>
Of course, who's going to be &quot;gatekeeper&quot;, who's going to determine who's allowed and who's not, is always a salient question in these matters, but usually, a community knows instinctively once a space has become &quot;unsafe&quot;, or when it's been &quot;overrun&quot;.  (Gay bars often turn into straight bars as soon as straight people discover they're &quot;hip&quot; places to be.  In fact, gay people are often annoyed by the phenomenon, and refer derisively to straight people in gay bars as &quot;visiting the zoo to view the animals,&quot; which often captures the attitue pretty well.  Might be a comparison on our server...)<br>
<br>
Firiona Vie is our &quot;safe&quot; space, as roleplayers.  The question is how do we, as roleplayers, keep it a viable safe space?<br>
<br>
Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crime Lord</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/1/02 4:19:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Roleplaying Preferred&quot; and Identity Politics</span><hr size=1> I think this should be in Rant Hall.  <p>Vall Shadowstrife<BR>
