<br>
This was several years back, but I was in an area where there wasn't a GLBT community.  It was GL and sometimes T, but B was left out because ... well, it wasn't always clear, but a lot of folks derided them as &quot;unable to be who they truly are&quot;, as if they were only halfway &quot;there&quot;.  I'm tremendously glad that garbage has been thrown out by the majority in favor of community-mindedness.  I'd like to see that happen here, too.<br>
<br>
