<br>
The key point is that FV is not an exclusive club, and it never can be, nor should it. Anyone who tries to put it in such a light is holding themselves above others, which is never a constructive thing to do. <br>
<br>
Think back to when you were in school (or, if you're still in school, think about the kids in your class). ... Does every one of them understand math like you do? Do they all write as well as you, or enjoy the same books? Do they type as well as you? Are all the kids as smart as you, or as dumb?<br>
<br>
Of course not. ... But do you look down on them because of it? If you do, then you're a jerk, just like you're a jerk if you question someone's ability to role-play in EQ, even on a &quot;roleplaying preferred&quot; server. We all have different abilities, different interests, and different perceptions of what constitutes the &quot;right&quot; way to do things.<br>
<br>
For some people, understanding all the subtleties in the EQ storyline and never dropping out of character is second nature, and they could do no less. ... Unfortunately, for all of us, they sometimes use this as a justification to be rude. For example, expecting someone to read their mind and utter the magic words in order to be worthy of their kindness or understanding (which, apparently, are not, &quot;Can I have a sow please.&quot;) <br>
<br>
